description: Visually inspect the internal area near the switches inside each control module, focusing on whether the absence of the indicator LEDs could have resulted in an open circuit (such as LED holders leaving a break in the intended main current path). Specifically, verify whether the switch and parallel LED circuit are truly in parallel with the through path, and check if the missing indicators or their holders leave a gap in continuity., outcome="All switch components (Control Switches 1–8) were visually inspected and found to be closed with no observable internal faults. For each control module, the 'Power Flow Indicator (green)' LED is physically absent and cannot be replaced. No information was provided indicating whether the absence of the LEDs or their holders has resulted in an open circuit or left a gap in continuity.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=240.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
